<!DOCTYPE html>

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head runat="server">
     <link href="default.css" type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <title></title>
    <style>
        .dpGreenHeader12
            {
	            background: GREEN;
	            color: White;
	            font-weight: bold;
	            height: 30px;
	            vertical-align: middle;
	            text-align: center;
	            text-indent: 5px;
            }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <form id="form1" runat="server">
    <div>
    <table style="width:100%;" border="1">
        <tr>
            <td colspan="4" class="dpGreenHeader12" >
                PRODUCTIVE DESCRIPTIONS
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>A</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>PRODUCTION</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                1
            </td>
            <td>
                Achievement of target</td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be capable of consistently achieving the targets. Additional/Lesser output produced will be taken into account.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                2
            </td>
            <td>
                Work completed on schedule
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be capable of completing the assigned jobs within the scheduled time. 
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                3
            </td>
            <td>
                Planning, prioritising and decision-making
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should organise themselves and co-ordinate with others, if required, to complete the jobs within required time to meet the schedule.<br />
                * Should also be able to take decisions after analysis of the customer requirements and keep line managers informed.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>B</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>QUALITY</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                4
            </td>
            <td>
                Internal feedback
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                The output should match the standard expectations of the internal departments. [Positive and negative feedback should be recorded in the feedback tab on MIS]
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                5
            </td>
            <td>
                Customer feedback
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                The output should match customer requirements. [Positive and negative feedback should be recorded in the feedback tab on MIS]
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                6
            </td>
            <td>
                Consistency in quality
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be consistent in delivering quality at all times.
            </td>
        </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>
                <b>C</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>DISCIPLINE</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                7
            </td>
            <td>
                Leave Management</td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should inform and plan leaves in advance ensuring that no excess leaves are taken and work is not affected. Values will differ for uninformed leaves, utilization of allotted leaves and having leave balance in ones account.  
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                8
            </td>
            <td>
                Punctuality
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be present at their seat in adherence to the shift timings allotted to them and should take breaks within the allotted time.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                9
            </td>
            <td>
                Work place ethics & adherence to policies 
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should restrict unwanted wandering in the production floor, unnecessary talking or standing in places other than their own; should behave gently with colleagues and avoid unnecessary quarrels.<br />
                * Should follow proper dress code, display ID cards and adhere to instructions, procedures and policies of the company.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>D</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>ATTITUDE</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                10
            </td>
            <td>
                Responsiveness to requests for service
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should be flexible to responsibilities or additional tasks assigned. <br />
                * Should get accustomed to any new role or responsibility given and provide his/her best.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                11
            </td>
            <td>
                Response to feedback
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have a positive approach to feedback given by superiors and take appropriate steps to improve ones understanding.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                12
            </td>
            <td>
                Team participation
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should be a team player and be committed to the success of the team as a whole.<br />
                * Should be an effective participant in all activities organised by the company.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                13
            </td>
            <td>
                Relationship with managers & colleagues
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have a smooth relationship with superiors and colleagues and only have healthy arguments by avoiding non-productive/unnecessary arguments with superiors and colleagues.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <b>E</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>TECHNICAL SKILLS</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                14
            </td>
            <td>
                Job knowledge & technical expertise
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should have good knowledge about the processes and the requirements of the customers.<br />
                * Should have good technical knowledge to solve any unexpected errors occurring during work, raise it to superiors and should not be dependent on others always.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                15
            </td>
            <td>
                Knowledge sharing and on-the-job training
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should be able to serve as a Mentor and transfer their work knowledge to colleagues and junior staff. 
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                16
            </td>
            <td>
                Interest to acquire additional training and development
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have an interest to learn new technologies and higher level requirements.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                17
            </td>
            <td>
                Problem analysis and initiative to streamline processes
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                *  Should be able to analyse problems, find the root cause of the problem and also suggest preventive actions.<br />
                * Should take initiative to streamline the workflow processes.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                18
            </td>
            <td>
               Implementation of tools and adherence to workflow procedures
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should use MIS to enter production details.<br />
                * Should use all tools that are part of the workflow procedure to avoid process violation.
            </td>
        </tr>
         <tr>
            <td>
                <b>F</b>
            </td>
            <td style="text-align:center;">
                <b>COMMUNICATION SKILLS</b>
            </td>
            <td  style="text-align:center;" colspan="2">
                <b>DESCRIPTIONS</b>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                19
            </td>
            <td>
                Oral communication
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                Should have excellent oral communication skills to converse in English.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                20
            </td>
            <td>
                Written communication
            </td>
            <td colspan="2">
                * Should be able to read and understand customer instructions correctly.<br />
                * Should be able to write in English without typos and basic grammatical errors.
            </td>
        </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    </form>
</body>
</html>
